`removeIntersection` requires both columns to share the same projection; if they differ, the method will throw an error. You can catch this error as follows:
```
// We start a SimpleDB instance
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
const table = sdb.newTable();
await table.loadGeoData("./geodata1.geojson"); // projection A
await table.loadGeoData("./geodata2.geojson"); // projection B
try {
  await table.removeIntersection("geomA", "geomB", "result");
} catch (err) {
  console.error("Projection mismatch error:", err.message);
}
await sdb.done();
```

Enable dark mode by setting the `dark` option to true.
