Calling `hasColumn` before loading data will always return `false` because no columns exist yet. Example:
```
// We start a SimpleDB instance
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
// We create a new table
const table = sdb.newTable("emptyTable");
// Check for a column before loading data
const exists = await table.hasColumn("price");
console.log(exists); // false
// Now load data and check again
await table.loadData("./data.csv");
const existsAfter = await table.hasColumn("price");
console.log(existsAfter); // true or false depending on the file
// We close everything
await sdb.done();
```

Here's how to set fixed y-axis scales for small multiples using the `fixedScales` option:
