The 'haversine' method is faster but less accurate, while 'spheroid' is more accurate but slower. Both require EPSG:4326 data.
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
// We start a SimpleDB instance
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
// We create a new table
const table = sdb.newTable("geoTable");
// We load geospatial data from a file (must be EPSG:4326)
await table.loadGeoData("./my-geodata.geojson");
// Example using both methods for comparison
// Haversine method
await table.distance("point1", "point2", "haversine_dist", { method: "haversine" });
// Spheroid method
await table.distance("point1", "point2", "spheroid_dist", { method: "spheroid" });
// Log the results
await table.logTable();
// We close everything
await sdb.done();
```

